-- Canadian Oil Discounts Weaken Ahead of U.S. Refinery Maintenance
-- B y   A a r o n   C l a r k
-- 2012-03-06T19:29:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-06/canadian-oil-discounts-weaken-ahead-of-u-s-refinery-maintenance.html
Discounts for Canadian oil widened
ahead of maintenance scheduled to begin next month at U.S.
refineries in the Midwest that process oil from  Alberta .  Citgo Petroleum Corp. will shut most of the production
units at its  refinery  in Lemont,  Illinois , near the end of April
for planned repairs, two people familiar with refinery
operations said Feb. 8.  BP Plc (BP/)  plans repairs on a crude unit in
April at the Whiting  refinery  in  Indiana , a person familiar with
operations said Feb. 3.  Syncrude (USCSSYNS) ’s discount to U.S. benchmark West Texas
Intermediate widened $2.50 to $8 a barrel at 2:08 p.m. in  New
York , the largest gap since Feb. 27, according to data compiled
by Bloomberg.  Western Canada Select (USCSWCAS) ’s discount slipped $1 to $33.50 a
barrel below WTI, the biggest margin in a month. The discount
for Bakken oil widened $4 to $19.  Enbridge Inc. (ENB)  plans to return Line 14 to service early
today and Line 64 on March 8, according to a person with
knowledge of the situation. The Calgary-based company halted
crude deliveries on Lines 14 and 64 on March 3 after two
vehicles collided, starting a fire at the pumping station near
New Lenox, Illinois, 36 miles (58 kilometers) southwest of
 Chicago .  In the U.S. Gulf Coast,  Light Louisiana Swee (USCSLLSS) t’s premium to
WTI narrowed 20 cents to $19.25 a barrel.  Heavy Louisiana Sweet (USCSHLSE) 
strengthened 75 cents to a premium of $21.40.  Thunder Horse’s premium to WTI narrowed 25 cents to $18.25
and  Mars Blend (USCSMARS)  strengthened 25 cents to a premium of $14.
Poseidon’s premium narrowed 10 cents to $13.25. Southern Green
Canyon’s premium lost 75 cents to $13.25 over WTI.  West Texas Sour (USCSWTSM) ’s discount widened 50 cents to $4.65 a
barrel.  To contact the reporter on this story:
